title.17: The Mutant Misadventures of Cloak and Dagger (1988) #17
title.81: The Mutant Misadventures of Cloak and Dagger (1988) #16
title.89: Master of Kung Fu: Bleeding Black (1990) #1

description.0: Thor fights his way through deadly foes to confront Loki at last!
description.4: The Fantastic Four find themselves taken captive by the enigmatic cosmic benig known only as Kubik! Can they overcome Kubik's mysterious challenges and escape once and for all?
description.5: The Starjammers led by a mysterious Warlord force their way on the royal Behemoth flagship in order to turn back the Shi'ar Throne to Lilandra!
description.6: Wolverine holding up a casino for their money? Is it Logan himself perpetrating this crime, or a rogue doppelgänger that holds many of his same powers?
description.10: Eddie Brock is back...for Peter's head! After escaping prison, Venom taunts Spider-Man into a final showdown. Peter Parker's known for his smarts- why then does he stumble straight into Venom's trap?
description.11: The team's final battle against the Tetrarchs of Entropy! Thor and Sersi remain in the Unspeakable One's dimension to destroy the entities of Entropy once and for all. On Earth, the Avengers help Rage rescue his kidnapped grandmother.
description.12: Receiving a tip that Demoliton-Man may have been discovered frozen somewhere in the northern polar ice cap, Captain America journeys to the Arctic Tundra encountering a sinister Ice-Worm and his old Liberty Legion ally, Jack Frost.
description.15: Saracen proves less than "honorable" while on a mission in the Middle East. Punisher’s there too, trying to prevent a skirmish over a powerful artillery weapon.
description.20: What if Wolverine had become the Lord of the Vampires? When Logan is turned to a vampire, he goes on to be the most ruthless one ever, topping even Dracula. How will this new threat shake the world?
description.26: Note: this issue contains only the Weapon X story by Barry Windsor-Smith.
description.27: Please note this story WEAPON X Experiment X is underway and some of the program's shadowy operators have their eye on Logan…
description.28: Doctor Doom has returned! The maniacal monarch has captured FF member Sharon Ventura, and the Four will have to endure a ganutlet of death in Latveria to save her!
description.30: Adam Warlock tries to stop Drax the Destroyer from living up to his name and putting an end to Soul World, while the Surfer receives a distressing warning from Mephisto.
description.33: Doctor Strange is the only line of defense between the Earth and the interdimensional menace of THE POSSESSORS!
description.37: Costume swap! Daredevil becomes Bullseye to frame his enemy.
description.39: As the Hulk, Doc Samson and Ringmaster celebrate the successful merge of the Hulk personas, the trio is attacked by the Pantheon!
description.40: When the mad scientist Kearson Dewitt creates his own ultimate power armor to take down Iron Man, Jim Rhodes must become Iron Man to save Tony Stark!
description.42: Loki strikes a deal with Mephisto - the power of the Wrecking Crew, in exchange for ambushing Ghost Rider!
description.44: Although Iceman decides to save Opal without any help, Jean and Mariko intend to quietly follow him.
description.47: Zaladane has erected six towers in the Savage Land and is now in sync with earth's magnetic field. With her magnetic powers she has scrambled all communication within the Savage Land, and the effects of her mad quest for power are already felt far away!
description.48: The conclusion to "Blood and Claws!" Wolvie is trapped in 1937 in the midst of a Civil War with no ways of getting back to his current time…
description.55: Punisher must get the drop on a group of Neo-Nazis before they obtain a WWII-era particle beam… that Microchip’s dad helped create!
description.56: Justin Hammer double-crosses Spider-Man, leaving our hero pinned against a wall by Boomerang! Will Spidey be able to neutralize both Cardiac and this new threat? Venom's symbiote re-emerges.
description.57: Trapped in exile, and separated from each other, the Avengers must stand alone against the Tetrarchs of Entropy. Back on earth, the Unspeakable One aligns himself with local hoodlums and takes Rage's grandmother hostage!
description.58: Captain America chases Father Time across an unknown dimension! Little does he know, it's merely an illusion to get him out of the house while the rest of the Avengers plan a surprise birthday party! Plus: the retelling of Cap's adventure with Sgt. Fury and his Howling Commandos!
description.60: Surtur's demons look to scourch the Earth. Can She-Hulk, Hercules and Thor stop them?
description.66: Drax and the Surfer wake up in the strange, alien Soul World after taking a beating from Thanos.
description.67: A powerful incantation requires powerful materials…and only Doctor Strange can acquire them! The first -- fur of a werewolf, from none other than Jack Russell, the WEREWOLF BY NIGHT!
description.70: Nyla is held as Kingpin's bounty, and Matt must get her back by entering the ring! After an unexpected outcome, Daredevil gets a glimmer of his memory.
description.71: Kitty reveals more of herself than intended at St. Searle's School for Young Ladies!
description.72: It's the most wonderful time of the year- for all but Rhino! What happens when the Gray Hulk bumps into the Rhino at a department store...where the villain is masquerading as Santa Claus?!
description.73: Things are getting desperate for the Iron Avenger as he suffers from major damage to his nervous system! He's running out of time to locate and defeat his enemy? Will Tony Stark survive the day?
description.74: The real Juggernaut finally shows his face! It will take every ounce of power in Thor's mighty hammer to lay low an unstoppable force!
description.76: Iceman and Opal are suddenly attacked by Japanese cyborgs, who throw Bobby out of the window and kidnap Opal!
description.78: Following the X-Tinction Agenda the X-Men, X-Factor and the New Mutants contemplate their next moves against the various threats facing them from around the globe.
description.79: Wolverine and Puck get to meet Ernest Hemingway!
description.82: A solo battle featuring one member of the Power Pack... left to stand alone against the Red Ghost!
description.88: Punisher and Microchip trail a madman killer who’s been offing cab drivers!
description.93: What if the Amazing Spider-Man married the Black Cat? But will Peter and Felicia have time for a honeymoon when rogues like Sandman and the Vulture discover Spider-Man's identity?
description.98: The newest anti-hero on the block is Cardiac- and he's going after white collar criminals! Spider-Man is on hand to stop him, but who's going to deal with the rampaging Rhino?
description.99: Avengers of the past and present re-convene to decide on a new team roster. Plus, Cap makes an announcement that will leave readers reeling!

2.text: The team’s downtime quickly comes to a halt when Ship is attacked by Apocalypse and his team.

6.text: Wolverine holding up a casino for their money? Is it Logan himself perpetrating this crime, or a rogue doppelgänger that holds many of his same powers?

9.text: Doctor Strange has captured Ghost Rider! What possible reason can the Sorcerer Supreme have for imprisoning the Spirit of Vengeance!

13.text: Sub-Mariner must defend himself, this time in court. His charge? Crimes against humanity!

14.text: The Fist of Khonshu meets The Spirit of Vengeance! Ghost Rider guest-stars in this giant-size issue!

16.text: She-Hulk is employed for her super human specialty in law to defend Meggan of Excalibur! Accused of property destruction and garbage consumption, Jennifer Walters will need to use all her expertise for Meggan’s case! And amidst these legal woes? A giant ‘trash monster’ running amok in London!

17.text: The unholy battle in the heart of Schamballah continues!

19.text: It's time for the West Coast Avengers to trim their roster down to SEVEN!

21.text: The cosmic assassin…revealed! Still mourning the loss of his father, Wendell finds himself completely unawares when assaulted by Maelstrom! A friend falls, and Wendell’s Quantum-Bands may be lost forever.

23.text: Fledgling hero Darkhawk fights against the demonic Hobgoblin! Guest-starring the Amazing Spider-Man!

24.text: WORLD OF MUTANTS PART 3 Even in the 31st century, the Phoenix holds sway! And the Guardians are about to find out why!

25.text: Emma Frost has her Hellions set their sights on former teammate Firestar. Will Angelica voluntarily return to her former team? Or does Emma Frost have another trick up her sleeve? The Hellions vs. the New Warriors in a battle royale you have to read to believe!

26.text: Note: this issue contains only the Weapon X story by Barry Windsor-Smith.

27.text: Note: this issue contains only the Weapon X story by Barry Windsor-Smith.

29.text: Spider-Man confronts the wild Wendigo. Wolverine guest-stars as the mythic monster makes a mess!

30.text: Adam Warlock tries to stop Drax the Destroyer from living up to his name and putting an end to Soul World, while the Surfer receives a distressing warning from Mephisto.

31.text: Nick Fury is tasked with infiltrating the Soviet's stronghold in the KGB. The Russians smell a mole among their ranks, and S.H.I.E.L.D.’s fiercest agent must investigate! Plus, the resurrection of Hydra!

32.text: This special What If? issue theorizes a Marvel Universe without the second team of All-New, All-Different Uncanny X-Men. Will the original five X-Men be able to carry Xavier's dream of mutant equality all on their own?

33.text: Doctor Strange is the only line of defense between the Earth and the interdimensional menace of THE POSSESSORS!

34.text: Iron Man and Captain America prevent a ROBOT HOLOCAUST!

35.text: Guest-starring the Fantastic Four! While the FF hold off Presence’s attack, Quasar pulls off a daring rescue of the cosmic refugees!

38.text: Rachel Summers is in danger of devolving into one of Ahab’s hounds! But will her transformation be catalyzed by a far more sinister force?

41.text: When Sunspot leaves, can the end be far behind? Featuring the first appearances of Feral and Shatterstar!

46.text: A Skrull stands revealed underneath Monster Island! But what has roped the new Fantastic Four and the entire Skrull army into a confrontation within the Mole Man's secret lair?

48.text: The conclusion to "Blood and Claws!" Wolvie is trapped in 1937 in the midst of a Civil War with no ways of getting back to his current time…

50.text: When teenager Chris Powell finds a mysterious amulet, he is transformed in to the superhero Darkhawk!

51.text: WORLD OF MUTANTS PART 2 The Guardians go toe to toe with the descendant of Wolverine- the mutant known as Rancor!

52.text: The Hard Choices saga draws to a close, but not before Emma Frost and her Hellions join the fray! Not only do the Warriors have to defeat Force of Nature, they must also save Speedball’s mother from certain disaster! Plus, Punisher and Night Thrasher’s duel hits a head!

53.text: Sub-Mariner, Cap, Human Torch and Thor fight together again! The stakes have never been so high.

54.text: They put him on trial, they tried to take his life, and now it's time for payback!

59.text: Ghost Rider and Danny Ketch merge completely and make their way out of Nightmare's Realm. But a certain Sorcerer Supreme is waiting for them when they get out!

60.text: Surtur's demons look to scorch the Earth. Can She-Hulk, Hercules, and Thor stop them?

62.text: The new Fantastic Four's investigation has taken them all the way to Monster Island, home of the dreaded Mole Man.  Will they find out the truth about the slain FF...or another set of secrets entirely?

63.text: Introducing for the first time, the Merc With a Mouth, the extra-lethal Deadpool! Plus, this issue also contains the first appearance of Domino!

64.text: The stunning conclusion to MASQUES! Will Ghost Rider and Spider-Man be able to set aside their differences to take down the Hobgoblin?

65.text: The Fantastic Four are dead!  Long live the new Fantastic Four - Spider-Man, Wolverine, Hulk, and Ghost Rider!? Can they get to the bottom of the FF's demise? And just what do the Skrulls want with this new team?

66.text: Drax and the Surfer wake up in the strange, alien Soul World after taking a beating from Thanos.

67.text: A powerful incantation requires powerful materials…and only Doctor Strange can acquire them! The first -- fur of a werewolf, from none other than Jack Russell, the WEREWOLF BY NIGHT!

68.text: What does the Red Skull have to do with a new incarnation of HYDRA?

69.text: Ghost Rider tries to stop the rampage of new serial killer known as Zodiak, while the mysterious Deathwatch joins with two new mercenary forces to take out the Spirit of Vengeance once and for all.

79.text: Wolverine and Puck get to meet Ernest Hemingway!

81.text: Cloak’s powers may be eating him alive. Dagger gets closer than ever to a dangerous gang leader!

85.text: Prince Namor has been captured in a container that absorbs every last bit of his strength! He must muster up every bit of his energy if he hopes to escape ALIVE!

86.text: Moon Knight confronts Bo Olisen, the man who set him up in the Trial of Marc Spector. He'd better hurry, however, because he's also forced to slug it out with a man called Chainsaw!

87.text: After escaping the men holding him captive, Frank Castle competes with the Monkey in a sniping contest.

88.text: Punisher and Microchip trail a madman killer who’s been offing cab drivers!

89.text: The Master of Kung Fu has been poisoned, and his only hope of survival is to track down the elixir vitae - his evil father's invention.

90.text: WORLD OF MUTANTS PART 1 After discovering the lost colony of Earthmen, the Guardians find themselves face to face with the deadly mutant called Rancor!

91.text: HARD CHOICES PART 2 Why is Punisher intent on seeing Night Thrasher eliminated? And after the two duke it out, who will remain standing? The New Warriors vs. Force of Nature, a super villain group with elemental powers!

92.text: A mysterious phenomena turning humans into robots casts doubt into the fate of humankind…

93.text: What if Silver Surfer had not escaped Earth? Mephisto makes an irresistible deal...

94.text: When Quasar interrupts the Jack of Heart's scheme of rallying refugees, an epic battle occurs!
